      <body>
         <div>
            <head>Intro</head>
            <p>This sample package uses Zotero API, DTS API, IIIF APIs, XInclude pointing to local
               and external resources to build with Xquery and FOP a PDF output. The result mixes
               information retrieved from the APIs. An additional layer of transformation is added
               to prepare inscriptions before inclusion which uses the EpiDoc example XSLT.</p>
            <div type="chapter">
               <head>chapter head</head>
               <p>This paragraph of text contains references to texts which assume a resolution
                  possibility in one existing DTS endpoint. <list>
                     <item>The following is a ref pointing to the Perseids DTS endpoint to print a
                        citation only. <ref cRef="Hdt" corresp="7.10" rend="cit">Herodotus book 7,
                           chapter 10</ref></item>
                     <item>The following is an empty ref pointing to the Perseids DTS endpoint to print a
                        citation only. The text of the citation is computed. <ref cRef="Hdt" corresp="7.10" rend="cit"/></item>
                     <item>The following is a ref pointing to the Perseids DTS endpoint to print a
                        quote based on that source. <ref cRef="Hdt" corresp="7.10" rend="quote"
                           >Herodotus book 7, chapter 10</ref></item>
                     <item>The following is a ref pointing to the Beta Masaheft DTS endpoint to
                        print a citation only. <ref cRef="Gen." corresp="43.34" rend="quote"
                           >Genesis:43,34 Ethiopian text</ref></item>
                     <item>The following is a ref pointing to the Beta Masaheft DTS endpoint to
                        print a quote based on that source. <ref cRef="BML acq. 810" corresp="12r"
                           rend="cit">Manuscript BML acq. 810, folio 12 recto</ref></item>
                     <item><ref cRef="BML acq. 810" corresp="12r" rend="quote">Manuscript BML acq.
                           810, folio 12 recto</ref></item>
                     <item>The following is a ref pointing to the Alpheios DTS endpoint to print a
                        citation only.<ref cRef="Aesch" corresp="221" rend="cit">Aeschilus,
                           Prometeus Bound, verse 221</ref></item>
                  </list>
               </p>
               <p> You can use here <list>
                     <item><ref target="http://www.thelevantinefoundation.co.uk"/></item>
                     <item>ref with type figure, internal, manuscript, work with respectively the
                        ids of a figure in a figure element, a chapter or any other node with a
                        xml:id, a manuscript in BM a work in BM</item>
                     <item><bibl><ptr target="bm:Meinardus1961Monks"/><citedRange unit="page"
                              >117</citedRange></bibl></item>
                     <item><placeName ref="LOC6126WadinN"/></item>
                     <item><persName ref="PRS7185Mosesof"/></item>
                     <item><note>to make a footnote</note></item>
                     <item>lists like this one</item>
                     <item>cit and quote</item>
                  </list>
               </p>
               <div type="section">
                  <head>section head</head>
                  <p>my section text</p>
               </div>
            </div>
         </div>
